DOC.brief_summary: This crossover investigation enrolls healthy volunteers and compares the exhaled oxygen content (FeO2) between the non-rebreather mask at the flush rate and a bag-valve-mask device at the flush rate, used with active positive pressure assistance.
DOC.brief_title: Non-rebreather at Flush Rate Compared to Bag Valve Mask With Assist
DOC.criteria: Age >17 Pregnant Any facial hair more than stubble that might impede a mask seal
